WHY GPL-3.0 (and not MIT): this distribution links Frahan.Kintsugi.Port, which is
a GPL-3.0 port of PuzzleFusion++. Under the GPL, the combined/distributed work is
GPL-3.0. If Kintsugi.Port is removed or isolated behind a separate build, the rest
of the codebase may be relicensed; until then the whole repo is GPL-3.0.

NOTE TO MAINTAINER: replace this notice with the FULL canonical GPL-3.0 text
(https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt) before the public release; this header
states the license and intent but the complete text must accompany the repo.

DATASETS in data/ carry their OWN upstream licenses (see data/ATTRIBUTION.md) and
are NOT covered by this code license; honor each dataset's terms (several are
non-commercial or research-only).
