THIRD-PARTY AND COMPONENT LICENCES (NOTICE)

(a) Frahan.Kintsugi.Port + kintsugi.bin weights — upstream PuzzleFusion++ terms.
    The upstream licence (vendored at
    src/Frahan.Kintsugi.Port/Weights/puzzlefusion-plusplus/LICENSE) states the
    code, data and model weights are NOT allowed for commercial usage; for
    research purposes the terms follow GPLv3. These terms cover the ported C#
    code AND the converted weights (kintsugi.bin). This is stricter than plain
    GPL-3.0; where the "WHY GPL-3.0" note above describes Kintsugi.Port as
    GPL-3.0, the upstream non-commercial restriction additionally applies.
    Frahan.Kintsugi.Port and kintsugi.bin are distributed SEPARATELY as an
    optional research package and are not part of any commercial offering.
    See src/Frahan.Kintsugi.Port/LICENSE.txt.

(b) Xbim.Essentials (IFC export) — CDDL-1.0. CDDL is a file-level copyleft
    licence with known GPL-compatibility friction. GeometryGymIFC is the
    planned licence-clean alternative for the IFC terminal.

(c) CGAL components used via frahan_cgal.dll include GPL-licensed CGAL
    packages (notably corefinement / boolean operations). See
    wiki/specs/20_frahan_cgal_audit.md in the orchestration workspace
    (D:/code_ws) for the per-package audit.

(d) The vendored Jigsaw_matching subtree under
    src/Frahan.Kintsugi.Port/Weights/puzzlefusion-plusplus/ has an unaudited
    licence; see the NOTICE.md beside it. Treated as research-only until
    audited.
